-- Turkish Stocks: Fenerbahce, Mardin Cimento, Park Elektrik Move
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-05-07T15:59:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-07/turkish-stocks-fenerbahce-mardin-cimento-vestel-beyaz-move.html
Turkey ’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  fell 0.4 percent to 58,809.68 at the close in Istanbul,
extending its lowest level since Jan. 31.  The following shares were active. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  Fenerbahce Sportif Hizmetler Sanayi & Ticaret AS (FENER)  , the merchandising arm of Istanbul soccer club Fenerbahce,
jumped 7.9 percent to 58 liras after the team defeated league
rival Trabzonspor. Fenerbahce’s 3-1 win yesterday puts the team
in second place behind league leader Galatasaray, according to
information on the website of the Turkish Football Federation.
The two teams play each other May 12 in Istanbul.  Mardin Cimento Sanayii & Ticaret AS (MRDIN)  , a cement
producer, fell the most since August, dropping 4.4 percent to
6.60 liras after reporting a 60 percent drop in first-quarter
profit to 6.7 million liras ($3.8 million), missing estimates.  Park Elektrik Uretim Madencilik Sanayi & Ticaret AS (PRKME)  , a Turkish mining company, rose to the highest since its
listing in 1997, gaining 7.5 percent to 5.76 liras after
announcing a plan to pay 0.67 lira gross dividend per share on
May 31.  To contact the reporter on this story:
